REV	INDIVIDUAL ASSESSMENT INDICATOR	"Indicator that shows whether the client's exposure should be assessed on an individual basis.
As a group policy, indicator should be ""Yes"" for non-retail clients if the total exposure of the client / client group is above 0,4 M EUR, or above 1 M EUR for clients financed only with standardized products. Lower local practice is allowed if the new threshold covers at least 80% of the portfolio; indicator should be ""Yes"" for these clients as well. In any other cases, indicator should be ""No"".
When calculating the threshold, exposure reported in the BS (on gross amortized cost / fair value loans), and exposure reported amongst the off-balance items (such as guarantees and unused credit lines) should be considered together. In case of a partial write-off, the gross exposure should be considered. In case of a full write-off, volumes should be omitted from the calculation."
